    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The AI tries to build it's defenses as close as possible to the last battle encounter IIRC. I agree this looking weird however if the AI ends up constantly attacked/ing from a single direction. The difference between RA2 AI and OpenRA AI is this distinction, RA2 AI lacked a special defense-placement logic.\r\n\r\nThe RA2 AI building placement logic was also weird, in regards of expansions - it couldn't utilize them properly. The AI tried to build a base around the last placed building. If it managed to build up an expansion somehow (via deploying a picked up MCV or Ares-onwards by activating a superweapon which delivered a building far away from the base) it immediately abandoned it's old base.\r\n\r\nThe RA2 ProtectWithWalls AI logic was bugged, sometimes if the AI lost the building desired to be protected, it started to fill the foundation of it with walls. Really amusing when you see squares of walls at an AI base.\r\n\r\nThe AI has emergency backup power capabilities, however the amount of power it stores to do that is a fixed value (and doesn't scale in regards to currently used power). It's IIRC around 60 but won't check it now, higher values end up with the AI starting with a PP-PP-Refi-Barracks build order, which has it's own letdowns (this backup power stashing logic takes priority over all build order plans)."
  },
