    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I definitely noticed that (both how weird the RA2 AI behaved and the OpenRA's weird power hunger build order). \r\nI do think there should be some sort of defense build circle for all non-MCV buildings though. One thing I definitely gave RA2 credit for was how it let you build near captured tech buildings (oil, machine shop, service depot, etc). I understand that it's a dated concept that can be easily exploited but, at the very least, allowing defenses to be built within their build range would be nice.\r\n\r\nNow that I've had more time to observe how the AI behaves, I noticed that they do make an extra reserve of power instead of just the bare necessities. But most (all) of the time, their bases can be destroyed by simply flanking them because they don't even make an effort to build where they last (or currently being) attacked. They just keep stacking those line defenses."
  },
