    "created_at": "2018-02-23T01:12:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-02-23T01:12:36Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> One other thing I noticed is that the AI only builds enough power plants to support almost exactly the amount it needs and never any emergency backup power. I could be mistaken with this observation though because I tend to lose track of how many power plants I destroy. Just thought I'd mention this since it sort of affects the defenses.\r\n\r\nAt least this part should be solved once #14594 is merged.\r\n\r\nAbout defenses, currently it simply places them in the direction of the closest enemy. One possible solution could be to make the AI cycle through the enemies instead, so 1st defense is placed in the direction of closest enemy, 2nd placed in direction of 2nd-closest enemy and so on. We could also require the AI to leave at least 1-cell gaps between defenses."
